Thinking about this part from the interview with the January 6 political prisoners. Article is from October. Imagine how this guy feels right now.

For an intellectual mutual here it is riding his car around and another used to skateboard daily for hours. It's what Dr. Ray Peat described in his Parkinson's "Tremulous Stiffness" newsletter. The perception of motion in travel stimulates the brain in a massive, coordinated way.

One of my friends (an Orthodox icon painter) told me he used to be a "troubled" boy back in the day and often skipped school to do mountain biking or just did bike tricks/stunts for hours at the park. Some men naturally need a "locomotion" hobby like this to keep them "grounded".

There is something in the free, pure movement through space that is incredibly grounding to this type of man and allows him to arrange his otherwise turbulent thoughts. A postural analog of a stimulant drug. Swimming (in a pool like Bobby Fischer), windsurfing all belong here.
